

Docker app running on vECS cluster behind a load balancer,heavily using DynamoDB.

improve the database performance by distributing the workload evenly and using the provisioned throughput efficiently. 


this is the intersection between scalable orchestrated apps and daabases

each partition key portion of a table's primary key determines logical partitions in which a table's data is stored

if a partition key design does not distribute I/O requests evenly, 'hot' partitions result is throttling and inefficient I/O use

the more distinct partition key-values theworkload accesses, the more requests will spread across the partitioned workspaces
and provisioned throughput will be used more efficiently as the partition key-value accessed to total number of partition key values ratio increases

more partition keys means more distribution and more spread access and efficient use of throughput

a composit primary key will helpprovide mor partition for the table and improve performacne

